root: ^There is a crumpled up piece of paper that looks like a handwritten note.
^I heard from Amelia that you’re doin’ good again.
^I hope this means you can get out of that awful place and come home soon.
^Phillip decided to move out to North Liberty so you won’t get to meet him, but my new boyfriend Derek is lookin’ forward to meeting you.
^He’s usin’ your old bed right now so let me know when you’re plannin’ on comin’ home.
